1. Executive Summary & Abstract
The "Elevator Pitch": Briefly state what NDP1 is and its primary goal.
Why BNB Chain? Mention the choice of BSC for its low fees, 3-second block times, and high scalability.
2. Introduction & Market Problem
Identify the Gap: Describe the specific market inefficiency or problem NDP1 intends to solve.
The Opportunity: Explain why "now" is the right time for this solution in the 2026 DeFi landscape.
3. Proposed Solution & Technology
Product Overview: Define NDP1’s core utility (e.g., governance, rewards, or specific platform access).
Architecture: Detail how the project uses the BEP-20 standard and any unique smart contract logic like anti-whale mechanisms or auto-liquidity.
Interoperability: Discuss how it integrates with the broader BNB ecosystem, including PancakeSwap for liquidity.
4. Tokenomics (The Core Section)
Token Details: Clearly list the Name (NDP1), Symbol (NDP1), and Network (BNB Smart Chain).
Supply & Allocation: Define the total supply and its distribution (e.g., 40% for Public Sale, 20% for Ecosystem/Liquidity, 15% for the Team with vesting).
Mechanisms: Explain any burning protocols, staking rewards, or transaction taxes.
5. Project Roadmap
Milestones: Use a timeline (quarters or months) to show past achievements and future goals like mainnet deployment, dApp launches, or exchange listings.
6. Team & Governance
Credibility: Highlight the team’s relevant experience in blockchain or the specific project industry.
